description:
While working on a study comparing different approaches to query the neXtProt dataset, I have observed that Virtuoso returns wrong results in some cases.
If I create the table —
create table test (
    id              varchar not null,
    pos_start  integer,
    pos_end    integer,
    PRIMARY KEY(id)
);

insert into test values ('ID1', NULL, NULL);
insert into test values ('ID2', 10, 20);

— then the SQL query —
select id from test where 0 < (pos_end - pos_start) and 100 > (pos_end - pos_start);
— returns an empty result. However, 'ID2' should be returned.

